body:
### Describe the bug

I was trying to import proportional (non-monospace) font to use with DELTARUNE. I modified `obj_writer` to fit my need (see the codes at reproducing steps)
This does some what worked, but the line on the first page of dialogue always overflows for some reason.

The first page of dialogue:
<img width="1375" height="220" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/460553f6-bb33-44ed-a653-606041e50cd7" />

The second page of dialogue:
<img width="1235" height="340" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2b4a729b-2148-49ca-8623-d91ecec27bd7" />

But however, if I do these following specific thing in the reproducing steps, the first page does not overflow anymore.
<img width="1357" height="420" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eda5f4f5-b0fb-404a-a8bc-e54e1c21df43" />
(This is a different dialogue but take my word for it)

### Reproducing steps

The bug:
1. Import the .YY gamemaker font files
2. Make use of the font in the fontmap in init_localization
3. Edit `obj_writer` to these following:
from:
```
else
                {
                charpos += 1;
            }
```
to:
```
else if (global.lang == "th") //this if for the Thai language which requires proportional font 
            {
                charpos += (string_width(thischar) / hspace); //To make it so that the current character is a fraction of the hspace so that newline does not end prematurely 
            }
            else
            {
                charpos += 1; //compatibility with other languages that do not use proportional font
            }
```

and
```
wx += hspace;
```
to
```
if (global.lang == "th")
        {
            if (ord(mychar) == 32 || ord(mychar) == 42)
            {
                wx += hspace; //Because the space and asterisk is monospace
            }
            else
            {
                wx += string_width(mychar);
            }
        }
        else
        {
            wx += hspace; //compatibility with other languages that do not use proportional font
        }
```
4. Run the game

To fix this
1. Import the font files and modify the init_localization in UndertaleModTool (under WINE)
2. Use the Avalonia fork of UndertaleModTool and modified the code

However, if I modified the font data using Avalonia fork, the bug would appear again, which made me suspect that it's actually the base UndertaleModTool bug

### Setup Details

1. undertalemodtool-0.9.1.0 under wine-11.12 and Avalonia fork which dates undertalemodtool-avalonia-2026.07.08 (native Linux)
2. Arch GNU/Linux
3. DELTARUNE
